For more information about this process, please go to Appendix A - Manage Asset Inventory Business Process to view the flowchart and process narrative. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Responsibility | |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Last Inventory Date , Last Inventory By , and Last Inventory Memo fields are automatically updated when: - · A Work Order with an associated Asset is changed to a status of completed - · An Asset barcode scan is imported into Maximo - · An Asset is manually updated in the Maximo Asset application To update the last inventory date, follow these steps: - Step 1. On the Start Center , under the Favorite Applications portlet, select Assets . - Step 2. The Assets application opens on the List tab. - Step 3. Search for the Asset (equipment) you want to view or update by entering information in the Filter Fields on the List tab.

Select the Select Date and Time (calendar) icon next to the Last Inventory Date field.

The Select Date and Time assistant appears. Figure 6. Select Date and Time Assistant Step 9. Select the appropriate inventory date and time, then select the OK button. The following data automatically populates: - · The Last Inventory Date field contains the date you selected. - · The Last Inventory Change By field contains the logged in VHA User ID. - · The Last Inventory Memo field contains data, such as 'Based on Manual Update by NXTECH_CLV'. NOTE : If a Work Order status is changed to completed and an Asset is associated to the Work Order, the Last Inventory Memo field will automatically populate with data such as 'Based on Work Order 12345.' If the Asset's Last Inventory Date is updated by RTLS, the Last Inventory Memo field will automatically update with 'Based on RTLS.

Figure 8: Toolbar - Save Asset Icon ## Update Asset Location An Asset's location is updated using the Move/Modify functionality in the Assets application. An Asset can be moved to a new location using a Work Order or directly in the Assets Application. When an Asset is moved from one site to another, a new barcode label will be generated using the new site's Station Number and applied to the Asset. To update an Asset's location, follow these steps: - Step 1. Select Assets from the Favorite Applications portlet on the Start Center .

Select Assets from the Favorite Applications portlet on the Start Center . The Assets application opens to the List tab. - Step 2. Type the Asset number of the equipment you want to move in the Asset field. NOTE: If you do not know the Asset number, type in at least the last 5 digits of the equipment number into the AEMS/MERS Ref ID (EE Number) field. - Step 3. Press Enter on your keyboard. - Step 4. Highlight the row of the Asset you want to move and then select the Move/Modify Assets icon on the toolbar. The Move/Modify Assets dialog box displays. Figure 9 . Assets - Move/Modify Icon - Step 5.
